I know this is fairly obvious to anyone used to writing web pages, but for joe public they won't realise.

The example in the [release notes|http://greenpeppersoftware.com/confluence/display/GH/GreenHopper+2.4+release+notes] is:

{quote}http: //...&staticView=true&versionName=Release 2.4&graph=5&fieldName=Story Points{quote}

No mention is made that you need to say:

{noformat}&fieldName=Story%20Points{noformat}

Created from this [forum posting|http://www.greenpeppersoftware.com/site/posts/list/191.page].

Last comment from JCHuet was:

{quote}I will surely have a look at the permission involved in GreenHopper and fix it if it does override JIRAs permission. {quote}
